The weather in London is generally mild and changeable, with cool to warm temperatures depending on the season.  

### **Current Weather (General Overview)**  
- **Summer (June-August)**: Mild to warm (avg. 18-23°C / 64-73°F), but can occasionally reach 30°C (86°F). Rain is still possible.  
- **Autumn (September-November)**: Cooling (9-18°C / 48-64°F), with more frequent rain and wind.  
- **Winter (December-February)**: Cold (2-8°C / 36-47°F), occasional frost or light snow, but mostly damp and overcast.  
- **Spring (March-May)**: Increasingly mild (8-15°C / 46-59°F), with occasional rain and sunny spells.  

### **Right Now (Today or Recent Trends)**  
Since weather changes frequently, check a live source like:  
- **[BBC Weather – London](https://www.bbc.com/weather/2643743)**

1. **BBC Weather** ([https://www.bbc.co.uk/weather](https://www.bbc.co.uk/weather))  
2. **Met Office** ([https://www.metoffice.gov.uk](https://www.metoffice.gov.uk))  
3. **Google Weather** (Just type "London weather" in Google search)  
4. **AccuWeather** ([https://www.accuweather.com](https://www.accuweather.com))  

### Typical London Weather:  
London has a **temperate maritime climate**, meaning:  
- **Mild winters** (average 2–8°C / 36–46°F)  
- **Cool summers** (average 15–25°C / 59–77°F)  
- **Rainfall**: Spread throughout the year, with occasional drizzle  
- **Unpredictability**: Weather can change quickly, so layers are always a good idea!
